caption.p:
GRB redshifts (z) vs. the values of peak luminosity of the bolometric light curve of the associated SN (



                     LP,SN

                  ). The plot shows the spread in data points and the lack of correlation between these two quantities.

GRB redshifts (z) vs. the peak time of luminosity of the bolometric light curve of the associated SN (



                     tP,SN

                  ). The plot shows the lack of correlation between these two quantities.

sec.p:
We address the observations of a sample of 24 spectroscopically well-identified SNe associated with long GRBs (GRB-SN). In Table 1, we give the name of the SN, the SN type, the cosmological redshift, our best estimate of E
            iso of the associated long GRB, the peak luminosity of the SN (



               Lp,SN

            ), and the time of occurrence of the peak (



               tp,SN

            ). We also give the analogous information from the literature.
